This directory contains Java source files for the Regalia Android application.

License classification by file:
  - StockfishNative.java: GPL v3 (derived from DroidFish)
      Engine management logic from DroidFish (ExternalEngine.java,
      InternalStockFish.java, UCIEngineBase.java, EngineUtil.java,
      DroidComputerPlayer.java). Copyright (C) Peter Österlund.
      Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      v1.0.2 additions:
        - _safeExecute(Runnable, tag): wraps _engineExecutor.execute()
          to catch RejectedExecutionException when the engine is
          mid-restart/shutdown. Notifies JS via onEngineError callback
          so the JS-side loading flags are reset instead of stuck.
          Used by engineGo / engineEval / engineHint / startPonder /
          importSettings.
        - stopAndWaitForBestmove(callerTag): blocks the calling thread
          until the engine's in-flight `go` command emits its bestmove,
          used by importSettings() before applying new settings so the
          engine is idle and can respond to `isready` with `readyok`
          (previously the 3-second timeout silently dropped settings).
        - importSettings() now honors user-explicit threads/hash values
          by auto-disabling autoConfig for that apply cycle, preventing
          silent override by hardware detection.
        - onSettingsImported callback is the single source of truth for
          the import-result toast (file-picker entry path no longer
          shows a duplicate toast).
        - cleanupEngineResources() resets _isPondering,
          _discardingPonderBestmove, _lastPonderMove, _stopLatch,
          readyOkLatchHolder, uciOkLatchHolder — prevents the
          "AI never moves after engine crash" bug where a stale
          _discardingPonderBestmove=true flag silently discarded the
          new engine's first real bestmove.
        - detectBigCoreCount() result cached in _cachedBigCoreCount
          (CPU topology is fixed for the device's lifetime).
        - MultiPV progress callback uses StringBuilder instead of
          JSONObject for the high-frequency onMultiPVProgress path
          (10-50 info lines/sec during search).
        - applySettings() branches consolidated — only Threads/Hash
          differ between autoConfig/manual paths.
        - Dead API removal: postJsCallbackJson() (zero callers),
          ChessApp.checkEngineThreadCrash() + engineThreadCrashed +
          engineThreadCrashMessage (flag set but never checked).
  - MainActivity.java: AGPL v3 (original)
      WebView host, immersive mode, lifecycle, SAF file-picker routing.
      v1.0.2: REQUEST_CODE_EXPORT_PGN=1004 + _pendingExportType
      distinguish settings vs PGN export SAF callbacks.
  - ChessApp.java: AGPL v3 (original)
      Application class, crash protection, locale detection.
      v1.0.2: removed dead checkEngineThreadCrash() / engineThreadCrashed /
      engineThreadCrashMessage (heartbeat mechanism covers engine death).
  - ChessWebViewClient.java: AGPL v3 (original)
      Page load handler, JS bridge registration.
  - EngineService.java: AGPL v3 (original)
      Foreground service that keeps the engine subprocess alive on
      Android 14/15 (Xiaomi HyperOS 3) when the app goes to background.
  - TlsSecurityHelper.java: AGPL v3 (original)
      TLS 1.2+ enforcement helper for HTTPS connections to the Lichless
      Tablebase API on older Android versions (API 21-27).
  - RootDetector.java: AGPL v3 (original)
      Non-blocking root detection. The result is informational only —
      the app never refuses to run on a rooted device because it is an
      offline chess app with no sensitive data to protect. The check
      is reported to the user via the About dialog.

See the root-level LICENSE-AGPL v3, LICENSE-GPL v3, and NOTICE files
for full license texts and attribution details.

v1.0.2 NEW FEATURE additions:
  - StatsActivity.java: AGPL v3 (original)
      Fullscreen WebView activity that hosts the 📊统计 statistics page.
      Loads assets/stats.html and passes the game PGN + eval data + move
      records via Intent extra. Handles 💾HTML export, 🗃️import (Paste PGN /
      Select PGN File), 🗂️复盘, and 返回对局 button actions. Android back
      button finishes the activity.
      v1.0.2 updates:
        - 📂 Select PGN File button now opens ACTION_OPEN_DOCUMENT directly
          from StatsActivity (no longer bounces through MainActivity).
          onActivityResult reads the file and calls onStatsPGNFileRead(content)
          JS callback to refresh the stats page in place.
        - performHaptic() now respects the user's haptic preference (reads
          hapticFeedbackEnabled from "RegaliaEngine" prefs + system
          HAPTIC_FEEDBACK_ENABLED) and uses VibrationEffect on API 26+.
        - HTML export callback uses JSON encoding (not string concatenation)
          to prevent JS injection from filenames with special characters.
        - REQUEST_CODE_IMPORT_PGN=2002 for the in-activity SAF picker.
      This file is original Regalia code (AGPL v3) — it only hosts the
      WebView and delegates all PGN parsing to stats.html (which is GPL v3
      due to DroidFish-derived code).

v1.0.2 bug-fix updates to existing files:
  - StockfishNative.java:
      - _mrToUci() / promotion UCI letter: knight 'k' → 'n' (was causing
        false PV divergence and spurious variation attachments for knight
        promotions).
      - destroyForciblySafe() wrapper: Process.destroyForcibly() is API 26+
        but minSdk=21. Three engine-shutdown paths now use isProcessAlive()
        + destroyForciblySafe() instead of direct engineProcess.isAlive() /
        destroyForcibly() which threw NoSuchMethodError on API 21-25.
      - handleFilePickerResult() / handlePGNFilePickerResult(): switched to
        try-with-resources on BufferedReader (was leaking the reader's
        internal char buffer, relying on GC).
      - Removed dead stats code (~80 lines): getStatsPayload(),
        closeStatsPage() (instanceof StatsActivity always false since
        activityRef points to MainActivity), exportStatsHTML(),
        statsRequestReview(), _pendingStatsPayload, _pendingStatsHTML,
        REQUEST_CODE_EXPORT_STATS_HTML, and the stats-HTML branch in
        handleExportFilePickerResult(). StatsActivity has its own bridge
        for all of these.
      - Removed dead `if (_isPondering)` branch in processEngineLine
        (unreachable: stopPonder/stopAndWaitForBestmove set _isPondering=false
        before sending "stop").
      - Removed redundant { } blocks in handleBestMove switch cases.
  - MainActivity.java:
      - Removed pendingStatsImportRequest static flag and its onResume
        handler (stats import now stays inside StatsActivity).
      - Removed REQUEST_CODE_EXPORT_STATS_HTML from onActivityResult routing
        (handled by StatsActivity).
  - EngineService.java:
      - PREFS_NAME = "RegaliaEngine" (was "Regalia_prefs" which is never
        written to) — fixes foreground-service notification language always
        falling back to system default.
      - Removed dead `en` computation block in updateNotification() (read
        from wrong prefs file, value never used).

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev20 changes:
  - StockfishNative.java (Rev20, GPL v3): added 7 new @JavascriptInterface
      methods:
      • persistentSetSync(key, value): synchronous SharedPreferences write
        using commit() instead of apply(). Use for any data the user would
        notice losing (eval cache, current PGN). HyperOS 3 cannot SIGKILL
        the app before commit() returns.
      • persistentFlush(): forces flush of any pending apply() writes by
        calling commit() on an empty edit. Called from MainActivity's
        onPause/onStop/onUserLeaveHint.
      • loadEvalCacheSync(): synchronously reads the eval cache file
        (/data/data/com.Regalia/files/eval_cache.json). Returns null if
        file doesn't exist. Called at JS module construction for instant
        cache recovery.
      • saveEvalCacheSync(json): atomically writes the eval cache file
        using tmp + FileDescriptor.sync() + rename. HyperOS 3-proof.
      • renamePGNCache(oldName, newName): atomically renames a PGN cache
        entry's .pgn file AND its associated .tags.json file. Refuses to
        overwrite if target name already exists.
      • setPGNCacheTags(name, tagsJson): writes tags to
        pgn_cache/<name>.tags.json. Empty array deletes the file.
      • getPGNCacheTags(name): reads tags from .tags.json. Returns "[]"
        if no tags file exists.
      Modified listPGNCaches() to include tags in the returned JSON
      (pre-loads all tag files in one pass for O(N) load). Modified
      deletePGNCache() to also delete the associated .tags.json file.
  - MainActivity.java (Rev20, AGPL v3): added onStop() and
      onUserLeaveHint() overrides that call stockfishEngine.persistentFlush()
      and evaluateJavascript("_flushReviewEvalCache()") before calling
      super. onPause() also now does the same. This ensures pending eval
      cache writes are flushed to disk before HyperOS 3 can SIGKILL the
      app.
  - build.gradle (Rev20): re-enabled externalNativeBuild to compile
      engine_jni.cpp into libengine_bridge.so from source using NDK
      27.2.12479018.
  - res/xml/backup_rules.xml and res/xml/data_extraction_rules.xml
      (Rev20): added <include domain="file" path="eval_cache.json"/> and
      <include domain="file" path="pgn_cache/"/> to declare eval cache
      and PGN cache directory as user data for cloud backup / device
      migration preservation.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev17-19 changes:
  - StockfishNative.java (Rev17-18, GPL v3): added 7 new
      @JavascriptInterface methods:
      • persistentGet(key), persistentSet(key, value), persistentRemove(key):
        SharedPreferences-backed key-value store (kv_* prefix) for
        HyperOS 3-resistant persistence of JS localStorage data.
      • listPGNCaches(), savePGNCache(name, pgn), getPGNCache(name),
        deletePGNCache(name), deletePGNCaches(namesJson): PGN cache
        manager backed by /data/data/com.Regalia/files/pgn_cache/<name>.pgn.
  - MainActivity.java (Rev17, AGPL v3): no changes; backup rules are
      declared in AndroidManifest.xml (fullBackupContent +
      dataExtractionRules attributes).

v1.0.4 EXPANSION (this round) changes:
